memberdef.name: SCIP_DECL_MESSAGEOUTPUTFUNC
memberdef.initializer: void x (SCIP_MESSAGEHDLR* messagehdlr, FILE* file, const char* msg)

detaileddescription.para: generic messagehandler output function
Should be equal to SCIP_DECL_MESSAGEWARNING, SCIP_DECL_MESSAGEDIALOG, and SCIP_DECL_MESSAGEINFO

memberdef.name: SCIP_DECL_ERRORPRINTING
memberdef.initializer: void x (const char* msg, void* data)

detaileddescription.para: error message print method
This method is invoked, if SCIP wants to display an error message to the screen or a file

This function is independent of any message handler input:
msg : string to output into the file (or NULL to flush)
data : data pointer

memberdef.name: SCIP_DECL_MESSAGEWARNING
memberdef.initializer: void x (SCIP_MESSAGEHDLR* messagehdlr, FILE* file, const char* msg)

detaileddescription.para: warning message print method of message handler
This method is invoked, if SCIP wants to display a warning message to the screen or a file

input:
messagehdlr : the message handler itself
file : file stream to print into
msg : string to output into the file (or NULL to flush)

input:
messagehdlr : the message handler itself

destructor of message handler to free message handler data

input:
